<h4 id="runway_selection">Runway Selection</h4>
<div class="level4">
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Runway 01 is the preferred active runway, up to 10 kts of tailwind. </div>
</li>
</ul>

</div>

<h4 id="runway_change_operations">Runway Change Operations</h4>
<div class="level4">
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Runway changes must be coordinate with existing DEL, GND, TWR, DEP and APP controllers.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> If possible, hold aircraft on stand before a runway change operation.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> If an aircraft is already taxying on Twy C, offer the pilot the option to use the existing active Rwy or to enter the runway for taxiway direction change.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> If an aicraft as already passed an approach IAF fix, an APP or TWR controller should advise the pilot of the possibility of a runway change prior to the aircraft being on the final approach segment.</div>
</li>
</ul>

</div>

